      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a bit safe, haha. It's more like wholesome observations. Most comedy clubs want stuff that's a little more \"on the edge\" or plays into the real stereotypes people talk about in their daily lives. Like, more about the specific attitudes or the way people might judge them, or even just typical ways they deal with certain situations. Can you give me some stuff that's a bit punchier? Maybe something about how they interact with authority or just general personality tropes that people usually joke about?",
